  <text>
     <body>
     <div type="poem">
   <head>
      <hi>To M</hi>
      <seg rend="sup">r</seg>. IOHN HOLLAND.</head>
   <l>THou that art made of better temperd clay,</l>
   <l>Then <hi>Titan</hi> ere made any; who dost pay</l>
   <l>Thy youth to time, with greater interest</l>
   <l>Of vertue, then of yeares, and promisest.</l>
   <l>More goods, then are of faire <hi>Pandora</hi> fain'd;</l>
   <l>And hopes more beaut'ous then her boxe contain'd.</l>
   <l>Bee thou like <hi>Phoebus,</hi> or his bayes, and find</l>
   <l>The blind God, and blind Goddesse euer kind.</l>
   <l>Be such that I to take may euer long,</l>
   <l>So faire a Theme as <hi>Holland</hi> for my Song.</l>
</div>
